{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/blog/get-page-by-title-is-deprecated/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Jack Harner","description":"Jack Harner is a Freelance Web Developer & E-Commerce Consultant based in Denver, Colorado. Shopify, BigCommerce, WordPress Dev & More.","author":"@jackharner","siteUrl":"https://jackharner.com"}},"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>If you want to retrieve a WordPress page by its title you used to be able to do that with a nifty function called <code class=\"language-text\">get_page_by_title</code>. Well now WordPress has deprecated that specific function and you'll get a warning in your site's logs if you try to use it. I'm going to show you how.</p>\n<div class=\"table-of-contents\">\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#what-happened-to-get_page_by_title\">What happened to get_page_by_title()</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#how-to-get-a-page-by-title-with-wp_query\">How To Get a Page by Title with WP_Query</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#lets-go-over-the-code\">Let's Go Over The Code</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#make-your-own-get_page_by_title-function\">Make Your Own get_page_by_title() function</a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<h2 id=\"what-happened-to-get_page_by_title\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#what-happened-to-get_page_by_title\" aria-label=\"what happened to get_page_by_title permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>What happened to get_page_by_title()</h2>\n<p>The <code class=\"language-text\">get_page_by_title()</code> function was deprecated when WordPress released version 6.2 back in March 2023. The function was old and <a href=\"https://make.wordpress.org/core/2023/03/06/get_page_by_title-deprecated/\">apparently caused problems</a> where the function could be run before plugins and things finished initializing. This opened up the possibility that <code class=\"language-text\">get_page_by_title()</code> would return a page that the current user wasn't actually supposed to have access to.</p>\n<p>WP_Query is a much more advanced way of querying the database for post and post data and isn't susceptible to the same bugs.</p>\n<h2 id=\"how-to-get-a-page-by-title-with-wp_query\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#how-to-get-a-page-by-title-with-wp_query\" aria-label=\"how to get a page by title with wp_query permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>How To Get a Page by Title with WP_Query</h2>\n<p>Since you shouldn't use <code class=\"language-text\">get_page_by_title()</code> anymore, you can do it instead using <code class=\"language-text\">WP_Query</code> instead.</p>\n<p>You can achieve that by setting the <code class=\"language-text\">post_title</code> parameter within the <code class=\"language-text\">WP_Query</code> arguments.</p>\n<p>Here's an example WordPress Query to get a page by the title:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"php\"><pre class=\"language-php\"><code class=\"language-php\">\n<span class=\"token variable\">$args</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">array</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>\n    <span class=\"token string single-quoted-string\">'post_type'</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> <span class=\"token string single-quoted-string\">'page'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n    <span class=\"token string single-quoted-string\">'post_status'</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> <span class=\"token string single-quoted-string\">'publish'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n    <span class=\"token string single-quoted-string\">'posts_per_page'</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> <span class=\"token number\">1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n    <span class=\"token string single-quoted-string\">'post_title'</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> <span class=\"token string single-quoted-string\">'Your Page Title'</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token variable\">$query</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">new</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">WP_Query</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token variable\">$args</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">if</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token variable\">$query</span><span class=\"token operator\">-></span><span class=\"token function\">have_posts</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">while</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token variable\">$query</span><span class=\"token operator\">-></span><span class=\"token function\">have_posts</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n        <span class=\"token variable\">$query</span><span class=\"token operator\">-></span><span class=\"token function\">the_post</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n        <span class=\"token comment\">// Page found, you can access its properties here</span>\n        <span class=\"token function\">the_title</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// Example of displaying the page title</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">else</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token comment\">// Page not found</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"token function\">wp_reset_postdata</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// Reset the query</span></code></pre></div>\n<h2 id=\"lets-go-over-the-code\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#lets-go-over-the-code\" aria-label=\"lets go over the code permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Let's Go Over The Code</h2>\n<p>In the example above, we're setting the <code class=\"language-text\">post_type</code> parameter to 'page' to specify that we're querying for pages. You can adjust the post type according to your needs. The <code class=\"language-text\">post_status</code> parameter is set to 'publish' to retrieve only published pages. You can modify these parameters as required.</p>\n<p>The <code class=\"language-text\">posts_per_page</code> parameter is set to 1 to retrieve only one page matching the title. If you expect multiple pages with the same title, you can increase this value.</p>\n<p>Finally, the <code class=\"language-text\">post_title</code> parameter is set to 'Your Page Title', where you should replace it with the actual title you're searching for.</p>\n<p>Within the loop, you can access the properties of the retrieved page using functions like <code class=\"language-text\">the_title()</code>, <code class=\"language-text\">the_content()</code>, <code class=\"language-text\">get_permalink()</code>, etc.</p>\n<p>Don't forget to call <code class=\"language-text\">wp_reset_postdata()</code> after the loop to reset the query and restore the global post data.</p>\n<h2 id=\"make-your-own-get_page_by_title-function\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#make-your-own-get_page_by_title-function\" aria-label=\"make your own get_page_by_title function permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Make Your Own get_page_by_title() function</h2>\n<p>If you've developed a theme or plugin that relied on the <code class=\"language-text\">get_page_by_title()</code> function that's now deprecated, you can substitute it for your own instead.</p>\n<p>Just define the function somewhere near the top of your theme's <code class=\"language-text\">functions.php</code>.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"php\"><pre class=\"language-php\"><code class=\"language-php\"><span class=\"token keyword\">function</span> <span class=\"token function-definition function\">jacks_get_page_by_title</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token variable\">$title</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token variable\">$args</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">array</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>\n    <span class=\"token string single-quoted-string\">'post_type'</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> <span class=\"token string single-quoted-string\">'page'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n    <span class=\"token string single-quoted-string\">'post_status'</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> <span class=\"token string single-quoted-string\">'publish'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n    <span class=\"token string single-quoted-string\">'posts_per_page'</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> <span class=\"token number\">1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n    <span class=\"token string single-quoted-string\">'post_title'</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> <span class=\"token variable\">$title</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n    <span class=\"token variable\">$query</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">new</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">WP_Query</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token variable\">$args</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">if</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token variable\">$query</span><span class=\"token operator\">-></span><span class=\"token function\">have_posts</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n        <span class=\"token keyword\">while</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token variable\">$query</span><span class=\"token operator\">-></span><span class=\"token function\">have_posts</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n            <span class=\"token variable\">$query</span><span class=\"token operator\">-></span><span class=\"token function\">the_post</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n            <span class=\"token comment\">// Returns the Post Object if one is found</span>\n            <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> <span class=\"token function\">get_post</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> \n        <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">else</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n            <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> <span class=\"token constant\">null</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n        <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"token variable\">$homePagePost</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token function\">jacks_get_page_by_title</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span> <span class=\"token string double-quoted-string\">\"Home Page\"</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>Then you just have to find and replace all of the old deprecated functions for your new shiny ones. Obviously you'll want to test thoroughly because this could potentially cause some bugs and behave slightly differently than the old function.</p>","excerpt":"If you want to retrieve a WordPress page by its title you used to be able to do that with a nifty function called . Well now WordPress has deprecated…","wordCount":{"words":389},"frontmatter":{"date":"January 20, 2024","updated":null,"title":"Function get_page_by_title is deprecated since version 6.2.0! Use WP_Query instead.","subtitle":"How to Get a Page By Title with WP_Query","tags":["WordPress"],"featuredImage":{"absolutePath":"/home/runner/work/jackharner-gatsby/jackharner-gatsby/content/blog/get-page-by-title-is-deprecated/ed-robertson-eeSdJfLfx1A-unsplash.jpg","childImageSharp":{"gatsbyImageData":{"layout":"fullWidth","backgroundColor":"#080808","images":{"fallback":{"src":"/static/4564b948bb4e0dcbcb47a62cf2c50d55/5267c/ed-robertson-eeSdJfLfx1A-unsplash.jpg","srcSet":"/static/4564b948bb4e0dcbcb47a62cf2c50d55/7284f/ed-robertson-eeSdJfLfx1A-unsplash.jpg 750w,\n/static/4564b948bb4e0dcbcb47a62cf2c50d55/29ba9/ed-robertson-eeSdJfLfx1A-unsplash.jpg 1080w,\n/static/4564b948bb4e0dcbcb47a62cf2c50d55/c8896/ed-robertson-eeSdJfLfx1A-unsplash.jpg 1366w,\n/static/4564b948bb4e0dcbcb47a62cf2c50d55/5267c/ed-robertson-eeSdJfLfx1A-unsplash.jpg 1920w","sizes":"100vw"},"sources":[{"srcSet":"/static/4564b948bb4e0dcbcb47a62cf2c50d55/57584/ed-robertson-eeSdJfLfx1A-unsplash.webp 750w,\n/static/4564b948bb4e0dcbcb47a62cf2c50d55/984df/ed-robertson-eeSdJfLfx1A-unsplash.webp 1080w,\n/static/4564b948bb4e0dcbcb47a62cf2c50d55/4a276/ed-robertson-eeSdJfLfx1A-unsplash.webp 1366w,\n/static/4564b948bb4e0dcbcb47a62cf2c50d55/9c00f/ed-robertson-eeSdJfLfx1A-unsplash.webp 1920w","type":"image/webp","sizes":"100vw"}]},"width":1,"height":0.6666666666666666}}},"ogImage":null},"fields":{"externalLink":"","externalLinkLabel":"Check It Out »","slug":"/blog/get-page-by-title-is-deprecated/","ogImage":"","date":"January 20, 2024","unlisted":false}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/blog/get-page-by-title-is-deprecated/","related":[{"id":"07f8bf3d-b5a9-5451-8c9d-80b83f192b4a","excerpt":"Here's how to get VS Code to automatically open a couple terminals in your different workspace folders when you first open VS Code. Open…","fields":{"date":"2024-06-18T17:07:20.364Z","slug":"/blog/auto-open-terminals-vs-code-workspace/","collection":"blog","published":true,"externalLink":"","externalLinkLabel":"Check It Out »"},"frontmatter":{"title":"How To Auto-Open Multiple Terminals In A VS Code Workspace","subtitle":"Get To Coding Quicker","tags":["Automation","Life Hacks"],"published":true,"featuredImage":{"childImageSharp":{"gatsbyImageData":{"layout":"constrained","backgroundColor":"#b8b8b8","images":{"fallback":{"src":"/static/18ca1a35e60ca2b2ffabdc2fef0f713f/def91/clement-helardot-95YRwf6CNw8-unsplash.jpg","srcSet":"/static/18ca1a35e60ca2b2ffabdc2fef0f713f/df91e/clement-helardot-95YRwf6CNw8-unsplash.jpg 131w,\n/static/18ca1a35e60ca2b2ffabdc2fef0f713f/9a46b/clement-helardot-95YRwf6CNw8-unsplash.jpg 263w,\n/static/18ca1a35e60ca2b2ffabdc2fef0f713f/def91/clement-helardot-95YRwf6CNw8-unsplash.jpg 525w,\n/static/18ca1a35e60ca2b2ffabdc2fef0f713f/2437e/clement-helardot-95YRwf6CNw8-unsplash.jpg 1050w","sizes":"(min-width: 525px) 525px, 100vw"},"sources":[{"srcSet":"/static/18ca1a35e60ca2b2ffabdc2fef0f713f/1b701/clement-helardot-95YRwf6CNw8-unsplash.webp 131w,\n/static/18ca1a35e60ca2b2ffabdc2fef0f713f/90103/clement-helardot-95YRwf6CNw8-unsplash.webp 263w,\n/static/18ca1a35e60ca2b2ffabdc2fef0f713f/a7b62/clement-helardot-95YRwf6CNw8-unsplash.webp 525w,\n/static/18ca1a35